<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>h4. What?</p>

<p>if you follow this step of the documentation: <a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/performance.classloading.html#performance.classloading.striprequires.sed">Classloading performance</a>.
Zend_Loader_Autoloader does not longer work!</p>

<p>h4. Why?
Because Zend_Loader_Autoloader requires Zend_Loader - but we strip out the required "require 'Zend/Loader.php';".</p>

<p>h4. Solution?
Change the documentation to something like this:</p>

<pre class="literal"> 
% cd path/to/ZendFramework/library
% find . -name '*.php' -not -wholename '*/Loader/Autoloader.php' -print0 | xargs -0 \
  sed --regexp-extended --in-place 's/(require_once)/\/\/ \1/g'
</pre>

